definition: to go forward/to advance/to go in/to enter/to put in/to submit/to take in/to admit/(math.) base of a number system/classifier for sections in a building or residential compound

to go/to go to (a place)/(of a time etc) last/just passed/to send/to remove/to get rid of/to reduce/to be apart from in space or time/to die (euphemism)/to play (a part)/(when used either before or after a verb) to go in order to do sth/(after a verb of motion indicates movement away from the speaker)/(used after certain verbs to indicate detachment or separation)
not to listen/to be deaf to

sentences.english: In most cases, it is a good idea to include them.
sentences.chinese: 大部分情况下，把教育时间写进去是个好主意。

sentences.english: After a Fan (mould) is made, pour molten bronze into it.
sentences.chinese: 等做好了范之后再把铜液倒进去。

sentences.english: She was caught trying to sneak into the bar and was booted out.
sentences.chinese: 她被发现偷溜进去该酒吧，之后被踢了出来。

sentences.english: They send in the robots to do the work.
sentences.chinese: 他们把机器人送进去完成工作。

sentences.english: Pushing it softly open and tiptoeing in, I found all quiet inside, and my wife fast asleep.
sentences.chinese: 轻轻地推门进去，什么声息也没有，妻已睡熟好久了。

sentences.english: He showed his identity card and went in.
sentences.chinese: 他把工作证亮了一下就进去了。

sentences.english: Put the flour in the bowl and then beat the eggs in.
sentences.chinese: 进一些面粉，然后打几只鸡蛋搅拌进去。

sentences.english: The barrel was nearly empty and I had to climb right inside to get my apple.
sentences.chinese: 苹果桶快空了，我只好钻进去拿苹果。
共同创造把人们都吸引了进去。

sentences.english: But she could not even get her head through the doorway.
sentences.chinese: 可是那个门洞小得连她的脑袋都钻不进去。

sentences.english: It is the museum of Hallstatt, but we did not go inside.
sentences.chinese: 这是哈尔斯塔特博物馆，不过我们没有进去参观。

sentences.english: No, Put the bag in first.
"Come, let's enter inside", the yogi said to his disciple.
sentences.chinese: “来吧，我们一起进去”，修行者对他的弟子说。

sentences.english: Come with me to take a look inside.
He went in carrying his suitcase.
I smiled at him vaguely and went inside.
sentences.chinese: 我对他敷衍地一笑，走了进去。
